{"TopicId":186791,"ForumId":16,"TopicTitle":"RTG and heat...","CreatedByName":"Jestersage","CreatedById":165777,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-07-28T01:21:31Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Jestersage","CreatedById":165777,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-07-28T01:21:31Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSo I am looking at making an \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Radio-isotope Thermo-electric Generator (a.k.a. Mars rover heating device)\u0022\u003ERTG\u003C/abbr\u003E enerator, and notice that it does generate heat\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSo the best\u00A0info I found is\u00A0\u003Ca href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/126334-rtg-heat-management/#comment-2295383\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003Ehttps://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/126334-\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Radio-isotope Thermo-electric Generator (a.k.a. Mars rover heating device)\u0022\u003Ertg\u003C/abbr\u003E-heat-management/\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNow at 1.7, assuming I am using 9 \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Radio-isotope Thermo-electric Generator (a.k.a. Mars rover heating device)\u0022\u003ERTG\u003C/abbr\u003E (for reasons, okay?), do I need thermal management?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Zhetaan","CreatedById":125721,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-07-28T02:04:42Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223642160\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022186791\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221564276891\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022165777\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Jestersage\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n38 minutes ago, Jestersage said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNow at 1.7, assuming I am using 9 \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Radio-isotope Thermo-electric Generator (a.k.a. Mars rover heating device)\u0022\u003ERTG\u003C/abbr\u003E (for reasons, okay?), do I need thermal management?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNo.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nRTGs reach their thermal equilibrium at, apparently, 350 kelvin of core temperature.\u00A0 That\u0027s\u00A0the temperature of an unbearably\u00A0hot room but it isn\u0027t enough to boil water, let alone damage your vessel.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Aegolius13","CreatedById":165625,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-07-28T04:02:12Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAs far I as I can think of, the only things that\u00A0require radiators (outside of deliberately bizarre builds) are:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n1. Drills\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n2. \u003Cabbr title=\u0022In-Situ Resource Utilization\u0022\u003EISRU\u003C/abbr\u003E Converters\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n3.\u00A0 Stuff in low solar orbit\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNuclear ENGINES used to heat up enough long-term to be a problem, but that hasn\u0027t been the case for a long time.\u00A0 RTGs are perfectly fine heat-wise.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Capt. Hunt","CreatedById":97860,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-07-28T06:59:47Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nRTGs have built in Radiator fins.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}